==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
According to ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi|Shuowen}}'', an {{Han compound|人|帚|又|t1=person|t2=broom|t3=hand|ls=ic|nocap=1}} – a person with a broom in hand.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|ss=⿰亻彐|alt=㑴,𢔀}}
Two Sino-Tibetan etymologies are possible:
* Cognate with {{cog|bo|སྟིམ་པ||to enter; to penetrate}}, {{cog|bo|ཐིམ་པ||to dissolve; to disappear; absorbed}}, though the two terms agree just as well with {{och-l|浸}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), or
* From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*syim||sweep}} (STEDT); cognate with {{cog|nun|śim||to sweep}}, {{cog|mhx|śam||to sweep}}, {{cog|my|သိမ်း||to gather in; to take possession of}}. Note the graph {{lang|zh|侵}} shows a broom ({{zh-l|*帚}}) which may carry a semantic function ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

